.TH vgsync 8
.SH NAME
\*Lvgsync\*O \- Synchronizes logical volume mirrors that are stale in  one or more volume groups
.SH SYNOPSIS 
.sS 
\*L/usr/sbin/vgsync \*VVolumeGroupName\*O \&...
.sE 
.SH DESCRIPTION
.iX "vgsync command"
.PP 
The
\*Lvgsync\*O command synchronizes the physical extents.
The synchronization occurs on the physical extents that are stale mirrors of
the original logical extent of the logical volume(s) belonging to
the volume group(s) specified by the
\*VVolumeGroupName\*O parameter.
The synchronization process can be time
consuming, depending on the hardware characteristics and the amount
of data.
Unless disabled, the mirrors within a volume group are synchronized
automatically when the volume group is activated by the
\*Lvgchange \-a y\*O command.
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
To synchronize the mirrors on volume group \*Lvg04\*O, enter:
.iS
vgsync /dev/vg04
.iE
